## Adjusting Conflicts During Play

### If Conflict Feels Too Easy

- Reinforcements arrive (makes narrative sense)
- Enemy reveals new capability (was holding back)
- Environmental complication (alarm triggers, ceiling collapses)
- Objective changes (villain escapes with the artifact)

### If Conflict Feels Too Hard

- NPC ally arrives (someone who'd realistically help)
- Enemy offers terms (most people prefer living)
- Environmental opportunity (escape route, environmental weapon)
- Reveal weakness (ancient armor has a crack)

Adjust for story and drama. The goal is memorable narrative, not mathematical precision.

